rule-4-14-a.test_description: Proposed building has one building segment and one zone.Computer room equipment power density exceeds 20 W/ft2. Expected result: PASS

standard.rule_description: A computer room is defined as a room whose primary function is to house equipment for the processing and storage of electronic data and that has a design electronic data equipment power density exceeding 20 W/ft2 of conditioned floor area.

rule-4-14-b.test_description: Proposed building has one building segment and one zone.Computer room equipment power density does not exceed 20 W/ft2. Expected result: FAIL

standard.rule_description: A computer room is defined as a room whose primary function is to house equipment for the processing and storage of electronic data and that has a design electronic data equipment power density exceeding 20 W/ft2 of conditioned floor area.
